eanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Oxton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Cheshire and Lancashire): habitational name from any of several places called Oxton, such as those in Yorkshire, Cheshire, and Nottinghamshire, which are named with Old English <i>oxa</i> ‘ox’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, settlement’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":41,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":50,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Ranulph de Oxton was born in 1174, in Kinderton, Cheshire, England, his father, de Oxton, was 35 and his mother, wife de Oxton, was 30. He married Agnes de Longville about 1194, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1240, in England, at the age of 66, and was buried in Hatton, Cheshire, England."},"et":{"1174–1240":"1174–1240","1174–1230"